version: 1
display_name: VCFE-9X-000210 - The ESX host Secure Shell (SSH) daemon must set a timeout count on idle sessions.
global_description: |-
  Setting a timeout ensures that a user login will be terminated as soon as the "ClientAliveCountMax" is reached.
osfinger: []  # API/proxy-managed control; not tied to a minion OS grain
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - VCFE-9X-000210
  srg:
    - SRG-OS-000480-VMM-002000
  cci:
    - CCI-000366
  nist:
    - CM-6 b
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_vsphere_esx:
    type: custom
    desc: The ESX host Secure Shell (SSH) daemon must set a timeout count on idle sessions.
    control_id: VCFE-9X-000210
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      From an ESX shell, run the following command:

      # esxcli system ssh server config list -k clientalivecountmax

      or

      From a PowerCLI command prompt while connected to the ESX host, run the following commands:

      $esxcli = Get-EsxCli -v2
      $esxcli.system.ssh.server.config.list.invoke() | Where-Object {$_.Key -eq 'clientalivecountmax'}

      Example result:

      clientalivecountmax 3

      If "clientalivecountmax" is not configured to "3", this is a finding.
    rationale: |-
      Setting a timeout ensures that a user login will be terminated as soon as the "ClientAliveCountMax" is reached.
    remediation: |-
      From an ESX shell, run the following command:

      # esxcli system ssh server config set -k clientalivecountmax -v 3

      or

      From a PowerCLI command prompt while connected to the ESX host, run the following commands:

      $esxcli = Get-EsxCli -v2
      $arguments = $esxcli.system.ssh.server.config.set.CreateArgs()
      $arguments.keyword = 'clientalivecountmax'
      $arguments.value = '3'
      $esxcli.system.ssh.server.config.set.Invoke($arguments)
